"""
S11 — HCR ROI pass/fail labelling GUI.

A single-screen ipywidgets labeller designed for ~2-5 s per ROI:

    +-----------------------------------------------+
    | sid=788406  hcr_id=14330  score=0.51  17/100  |
    | +--------+ +--------+ +--------+   features:  |
    | | 405    | | 488    | | overlay|   solidity  |
    | | xy MIP | | xy MIP | | mask   |   volume    |
    | +--------+ +--------+ +--------+   knn_d1    |
    | +--------+ +--------+ +--------+   peak_in   |
    | | 405 z- | | 405 z  | | 405 z+ |   ...       |
    | +--------+ +--------+ +--------+              |
    | [Good g] [Bad b] [Unsure u] [Skip s] [Undo z] |
    | last 3: good(14328) bad(14329) good(14330)    |
    +-----------------------------------------------+

Labels are appended to
    code/sessions/v3_S11_roi_quality/outputs/roi_qc_actions.jsonl
one JSON per row::

    {"ts": "...", "sid": "...", "hcr_id": ..., "label": "good"|"bad"|"unsure",
     "stage1_score": 0.51, "reviewer": "...", "session_token": "..."}

Resume detects already-labelled `(sid, hcr_id)` pairs and skips them.

Usage in a notebook::

    from gui import launch
    launch(sid="788406", n_rois=80, score_band=(0.3, 0.7), reviewer="alice")
"""
